3. Vale verified x86_64 assembly  (aesgcm-x86_64-linux.S, cpuid-x86_64-linux.S)
================================================================================

These files carry no per-file header. Per the HACL* README, the whole repository
is released under Apache-2.0, and the *generated C* code is additionally available
under MIT. The Vale assembly is verified assembly from the Vale / ValeCrypt project
(Project Everest), not generated C, so the MIT grant does not extend to it; it is
used under the repository-default Apache License, Version 2.0:

  Copyright (c) INRIA and Microsoft Corporation (Project Everest). All rights reserved.
  Licensed under the Apache 2.0 License.

The full Apache-2.0 text is the same license under which kroopt itself is released;
see the repository-root LICENSE file.

================================================================================
Provenance
================================================================================

Upstream:  HACL* / Project Everest — https://github.com/hacl-star/hacl-star
           (obtained via the `hacl-star` OCaml package, version 0.4.5).
Subset:    the primitives the constrained TLS 1.3 profile needs end-to-end:
           SHA-256/384, X25519, P-256 (ECDH + ECDSA), ChaCha20-Poly1305,
           HKDF/HMAC, Ed25519, and RSA-PSS, plus the EverCrypt AEAD dispatch
           layer and the Vale verified x86_64 assembly for AES-128/256-GCM, and
           the kremlin headers these include.
Changes:   none. The files are redistributed verbatim; their license headers are
           retained unmodified. kroopt's only added C is Kroopt/Native/kroopt_ffi.c
           (kroopt's own Apache-2.0 FFI glue), which is not part of HACL*.
